# High-Priority Rules
- Do exactly what was requested. Nothing extra.
- Keep changes minimal and local.
- Do not add files, dependencies, or abstractions unless strictly necessary.
- Do not refactor unrelated code.
- Keep domain logic separate from UI.
- Keep field names consistent everywhere.
- Do not hallucinate files, imports, APIs, or infrastructure.
- Prefer simple, boring solutions.
- Keep the product mobile-first, short-form, and practical.
